    <h1>OpenSLM</h1>
    <p class="lede">The Open Small Models Accord — ten principles for small open models that can be trusted at scale.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <p>OpenSLM is a draft accord, not a benchmark or a leaderboard. It is the set of properties that a small, open language model has to satisfy if it is going to be relied on by anyone whose institution can be sued, audited, or replaced.</p>
    <p>Drafting and review at <a href="https://openslm.ai/">openslm.ai</a>.</p>
